      • registerEventListener

        public def registerEventListener(listener : Object,
                                 fireInitializeEvent : boolean,
                                 filter : (Event)=>Boolean,
                                 initiallizationParameters : Object*) : void 
        Description copied from interface: InternalEventBusCapacity
        Register the given object on the event bus for receiving any event.

        If the filter is provided, it will be used for determining if the given behavior accepts a specific event. If the filter function replies true for a specific event as argument, the event is fired in the behavior context. If the filter function replies false, the event is not fired in the behavior context.

        Specified by:
        registerEventListener in interface InternalEventBusCapacity
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener on the SARL events.
        fireInitializeEvent - indicates if the Initialize event should be fired to the listener if the agent is alive.
        filter - the filter function.
        initiallizationParameters - the parameters to pass to the behavior for its initialization.
